  "prompt": "Why isn't the top answer on Quora the most upvoted one?",
  "response": "The top answer on Quora is determined by a combination of factors, including the number of upvotes, the recency of the answer, and sometimes the relevance or quality as judged by the Quora algorithm. It\u2019s possible for a less upvoted answer to be ranked higher if it was posted more recently or if it has been selected as a \"featured\" response by the question asker or by Quora itself. Additionally, user engagement metrics such as comments, shares, or views can also influence the ranking of answers. Therefore, the most upvoted answer may not always be at the top due to these various factors.",
